			<div id="post-7782" class="post-7782 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-survival-preparedness tag-firearms tag-guns tag-joe-nobody tag-shooting">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist" title="Permalink to Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &#8220;The Home Schooled Shootist&#8221;" rel="bookmark">Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &#8220;The Home Schooled Shootist&#8221;</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist" title="7:06 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">November 8, 2012</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist#comments" title="Comment on Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &#8220;The Home Schooled Shootist&#8221;">19 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton7782" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fjoe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist&amp;text=Episode-1016-%20Joe%20Nobody%20on%20%26%238220%3BThe%20Home%20Schooled%20Shootist%26%238221%3B&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fjoe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><div class="podPress_content podPress_content_audio_mp3">
<div class="podpress_playerspace podpress_playerspace_audio_mp3 podpress_mp3player" style="display:block;" ><div id="podPressPlayerSpace_3"><!-- podPress --></div></div>
<div class="podPress_downloadlinks podPress_downloadlinks_audio_mp3"><a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3" target="new" title="Download: Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &quot;The Home Schooled Shootist&quot;" class="podpress_downloadimglink podpress_downloadimglink_audio_mp3"><img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/audio_mp3_button.png" class="podPress_imgicon podpress_imgicon_audio_mp3" alt="" /></a> <span class="podpress_mediafile_title podpress_mediafile_title_audio_mp3">Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &amp;quot;The Home Schooled Shootist&amp;quot;</span> <span class="podpress_mediafile_dursize podpress_mediafile_dursize_audio_mp3">[ 1:04:59 ]</span> <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_3" class="podpress_playlink podpress_playlink_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressShowHidePlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &amp;quot;The Home Schooled Shootist&amp;quot;', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;"><span id="podPressPlayerSpace_3_PlayLink" class="podPress_playerspace_playlink">Play Now</span></a><input type="hidden" id="podPressPlayerSpace_3_OrigURL" value="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3" /> | <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_3" class="podpress_playinpopup podpress_playinpopup_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressPopupPlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3', 290, 24, 'The Survival Podcast', '7782', 'Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &amp;quot;The Home Schooled Shootist&amp;quot;', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;">Play in Popup</a> | <a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3" target="new" class="podpress_downloadlink podpress_downloadlink_audio_mp3">Download</a></div></div>
<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('3', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/11-12/epi-01016-joe-nobody-on-the-home-schooled-shootist.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-1016- Joe Nobody on &amp;quot;The Home Schooled Shootist&amp;quot;', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><div id="attachment_7789" style="width: 185px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/Home-Schooled-Shootist-Training-Carbine/dp/0615689493/ref=la_B00553BHW2_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1352311446&amp;sr=1-3"><img class="size-full wp-image-7789" title="shootist" src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/shootist1.jpg" alt="The Home Schooled Shootist by Joe Nobody" width="175" height="216" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Home Schooled Shootist by Joe Nobody</p></div>
<p>Joe Nobody is the author of several best selling books including “Holding Your Ground” ,”The TEOTWAWKI Tuxedo”, “Holding Their Own” and “Without Rule of Law”.</p>
<p>Joe has over 30 years as a government and private contractor experience and is a professional firearms instructor and competition shooter.</p>
<p>Joe Nobody&#8217;s latest book, &#8220;The Home Schooled Shootist, Training to Fight With a Carbine&#8221; is an instruction guide for intermediate to advanced shooters. It addresses fighting with shoulder-fired weapons at ranges 0 through 600 meters.</p>
<p>Of his new book Joe states, <em>&#8220;Shootist was written due to popular demand. It seemed like everyone who knows me personally kept up the pressure to write a book on gun fighting. &#8220;Teaching people is what you do best Joe,&#8221; was a common statement. Many readers of my other books corresponded with questions or requests associated with the contents herein. Still, I hesitated because from my perspective, few people will ever require these skills. Over the last year or so, my opinion changed.</em></p>
<p><em>We Americans have a long tradition of excellence with shoulder fired weapons. Throughout much of our history, marksmanship and bravery were enough. Those days are long behind us. Advancements in technology have raised the standard and despite droves of people purchasing military grade weapons, optics and accessories, few people develop the skills necessary to properly utilize these assets.</em>&#8221;</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Joes new book is divided into three basic sections:</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>How to create and execute eleven different drills that sharpen skills necessary to survive violent encounters</li>
<li>How to evaluate the results of these exercises</li>
<li>How to improve the operator’s capabilities</li>
</ul>
<p>The book covers topics ranging from sight pictures, on-range and off-range training techniques, and even rifle specific weight training.   This is a book intended for those who want to train at their own pace, using their own facilities. The drills are creative, unique and can be challenging. Detailed instructions are included on how to construct the various training tools and courses.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Resources for today’s show…</span></strong></p>
