			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/maglula-magazine-loader-from-mag-lula-butler-creek" title="Permalink to Maglula Magazine Loader from Mag Lula / Butler Creek" rel="bookmark">Maglula Magazine Loader from Mag Lula / Butler Creek</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/maglula-magazine-loader-from-mag-lula-butler-creek" title="2:00 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">November 26, 2010</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/maglula-magazine-loader-from-mag-lula-butler-creek#comments" title="Comment on Maglula Magazine Loader from Mag Lula / Butler Creek">11 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton2945" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fmaglula-magazine-loader-from-mag-lula-butler-creek&amp;text=Maglula%20Magazine%20Loader%20from%20Mag%20Lula%20%2F%20Butler%20Creek&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fmaglula-magazine-loader-from-mag-lula-butler-creek" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><p>I never really minded loading up a magazine or two for some basic shooting but when I spend a full range day it can get kind of old.  I have fooled around with a lot of magazine loading tools over the years but nothing until now really seemed to have a cost to performance ratio that I found acceptable.</p>
<p>About a month ago a listener sent me a video about the Mag Lula Magazine Loader for the AR15 from Maglula / Butler Creek wanting to know if it worked as good as it appeared to.  So I ordered one from CheaperThanDirt.com and I have not been disappointed for a second with it.</p>
<p>I figured with Christmas coming this might be a good time to post this review.  If you have a shooter in your family that shoots the AR of any of the weapons they make a loader for I can promise you they will love one of these.  You can find this loader and loaders for other guns like the AK, Uzi, MP5, Universal Pistol, FN FAL and others at this link <a target="_blank" href="http://amzn.to/eqnm4y">http://amzn.to/eqnm4y</a></p>
